      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Our working principles of user research <strong class="govuk-tag">Beta</strong></h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">These are the principles that, as a user researcher at DfE, you should always follow. <a href="/-principles/">Find out more about our principles, why they exist, and how we help you meet them.</a></p>
      <div class="cards card-thirds">
         <ul>
            <li class="card">
               <div class="text">
                  <h3><a href="/-principles/principle-1.html" rel="noopener noreferrer">1. We put all of our users at the heart of DfE’s work</a></h3>
                  <p>This principle is about <strong>researching in a way that is inclusive of all our users, and ensuring our teams hear and understand their needs.</strong></p>
               </div>
            </li>
            <li class="card">
               <div class="text">
                  <h3><a href="/-principles/principle-2.html" rel="noopener noreferrer">2. We do what’s right, based on evidence</a></h3>
                  <p>This principle is about <strong>being objective and challenging biases.</strong></p>
               </div>
            </li>
            <li class="card">
               <div class="text">
                  <h3><a href="/-principles/principle-3.html" rel="noopener noreferrer">3. We do high quality, safe and ethical research</a></h3>
                  <p>This principle is about <strong>ensuring we and our teams meet DfE's user research standards.</strong></p>
               </div>
            </li>
            <li class="card">
               <div class="text">
                  <h3><a href="/-principles/principle-4.html" rel="noopener noreferrer">4. We are team players, agile and collaborative</a></h3>
                  <p>This principle is about <strong>our ways of working in our teams, programmes and portfolios.</strong></p>
               </div>
            </li>
            <li class="card">
               <div class="text">
                  <h3><a href="/-principles/principle-5.html" rel="noopener noreferrer">5. We support each other, develop ourselves, and advocate for UR</a></h3>
                  <p>This principle is about <strong>learning and developing as individuals, and together as one DfE UR community.</strong></p>
               </div>
            </li>
         </ul>
